[h3 id=Summary 
	" Summary
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"This is a quick summary of what to know when submitting to the site. Further information is available below this summary if needed.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Verify that your movie works. Do not submit movies that even you can't view!
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Make sure your movie is a 
		[b 
			"finished, optimized product
		]b
		". TASVideos is an archive and a records site, not a leaderboard.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" Incomplete and suboptimal runs can be uploaded to 
				(__wikiLink|href=/Userfiles|implicitdisplaytext=Userfiles)
				". You can then share the link on the 
				(__wikiLink|href=/Forum|implicitdisplaytext=Forum)
				" or 
				(__wikiLink|displaytext=Discord|href=/DiscordServer)
				" to spark some discussion that may help you.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" You are considered the expert on your movie and game. It is highly recommended, though not required, to explain your movie in your submission text as much as possible and to answer questions posed in your submission's forum thread.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" We recognize and understand that this may not be possible for some submitters due to time constraints, language barriers, and/or other obstructions. Do as much as you're comfortable with, and we will accommodate.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" If you feel your movie might not be acceptable, consult the 
		[b 
			(__wikiLink|href=/Movierules|implicitdisplaytext=movie rules)
		]b
		" and the 
		[b 
			(__wikiLink|href=/Guidelines|implicitdisplaytext=guidelines)
		]b
		" for detailed information.
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" Note that any game, version, and branch may be submitted at any time, regardless of whether or not there's a prior entry on the site. All game and run information is manually catalogged to the site upon submission or publication, so there may not be any information about a particular game or game version until we have received a submission for it. 
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" If you find improvements to your movie or wish for the input file to be updated, upload the new version to 
		(__wikiLink|href=/Userfiles|implicitdisplaytext=Userfiles)
		" and ask a Judge to replace the file instead of re-submitting the new file.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Once you are logged in and ready to submit, head over to the 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Submit Movie|href=/Submissions/Submit)
		" page and fill out all relevant details.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[hr 
]hr
[hr 
]hr
[hr 
]hr
[h3 id=MovieFile 
	" Movie file
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Our 
	(__wikiLink|href=/EmulatorResources|implicitdisplaytext=Emulator Resources)
	" and 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Platforms|implicitdisplaytext=Platforms)
	" pages list all allowable input file formats. The site does not recognize any input file not on those lists, and as such they cannot be submitted. Please contact us if you have an input file format that you want to be supported!
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=AuthorS 
	" Author(s)
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The TASVideos username(s) of the author(s). Hit the 
	[code 
		"+
	]code
	" button to add multiple authors.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=ExternalAuthors 
	" External Authors
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This field is for author that don't have a TASVideos account. Separated with comma for multiple authors.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=GameVersionAndName 
	" Game version and name
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Please write the official name of the game. For example, if you are submitting a movie for the game Super Mario Bros., write 
	[code 
		"Super Mario Bros.
	]code
	". Do not write 
	[code 
		"Super Mario
	]code
	", 
	[code 
		"SMB
	]code
	", 
	[code 
		"Mario
	]code
	", or 
	[code 
		"Mario Bros.
	]code
	", since the names may be confused with other titles. If the game has a Japanese title (or other non-Latin writing system), write the most well-known romanization. For instance, Japanese titles are written using 
	[a href=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wāpuro_rōmaji rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Wāpuro rōmaji
	]a
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If the game has multiple revisions, please indicate the revision too. For example: 
	[code 
		"USA r0
	]code
	" or 
	[code 
		"USA r1
	]code
	". If you don't know the version, use the most appropriate option.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If your game, version, or revision does not have an entry on the site, you may still submit it. The relevant information will be catalogged from your submission.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=BranchName 
	" Branch name
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This is the category of the run you are submitting. Examples of branches include "100%", "playaround", and "game end glitch". Fastest completion (known as "any%") runs do not need to be branched.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Any branch may be submitted, though it is recommended to use names that are short, easy to understand, and consistent with other branch names.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=RomFilename 
	" ROM filename
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The ROM filename is important in verifying your submission. Ideally, it should be the 
	[a href=https://web.archive.org/web/20171217103043/https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoodTools rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Good Tools ROM set name
	]a
	", as it gives all of the necessary information about the game, the version, and the ROM dump. Example: 
	[code 
		"Final Fantasy III (U) (V1.0) [!].smc
	]code
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=EmulatorAndVersion 
	" Emulator and version
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"List the emulator you used, as well as the version. The version is important, as newer or older versions of emulators can affect your movie's sync.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=EncodeEmbeddedLink 
	" Encode embedded link
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"If you have a video encode of your run, you can put its link here. If you have several videos, see below for how to add them to the wiki text.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=CommentsAndExplanations 
	" Comments and Explanations
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"This is where you explain your submission. These comments are extremely helpful for both the Judges and the community to understand your run, so please fill them in as much as you possibly can. The submission page includes a "Prefill Submission Comments" button that provides a basic outline you can work off of.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The submission text uses a special 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=text formatting system|href=/TextFormattingRules)
	". Use * for bullet lists, ! for headings and put an empty line between each of your paragraphs. 
	[em 
		"Do not begin lines with spaces.
	]em
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The most important information to include is as follows. Omitting this information may lead to a more difficult judgement process:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Which emulator
		]b
		" did you use? Include the version as well!
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				" Which 
				[b 
					"emulator settings
				]b
				"? Please list every individual emulation setting which you have modified (does not apply to Dolphin users, see note below).
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" A 
		[b 
			"checksum of your ROM or ISO
		]b
		" (SHA1 recommended).
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[b 
			"Which BIOS
		]b
		" did you use? (Region and revision)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" If your movie needs some setup (e.g. prepare a memory card) to sync, provide a link to 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=the verification movie|href=/MovieRules#MovieMustBeComplete)
		".
		$LF
		[ul 
			[li 
				"Not applicable for all systems.
				$LF
			]li
		]ul
	]li
	[li 
		" For GameCube and Wii submissions: Dolphin comes with free 
		[b 
			"dsp_*.bin files
		]b
		" required for DSP LLE emulation; did you use these or the console ones (i.e. did you have to download the two dsp_*.bin files yourself from a non-Dolphin site)?
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"It is also highly recommended that you include the following information, as it significantly helps the Judges and the community to understand your game and your submission:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Explain any usage of game mechanics, such as using passwords, in game warps, taking damage, dying, or saving and restarting to save time. 
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Describe your goals and aims clearly. Are you collecting all items? Are you avoiding as many as possible? What is the movie accomplishing?
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" A brief description of your game helps people unfamiliar with it to understand your movie.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" If your movie is an improvement to an existing movie, please mention which movie it improves upon, how big the improvement is, and describe the improvements.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" If your game includes any content that may be unsuitable for some people or generally questionable, please include any relevant 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=content warnings|href=/ContentWarnings)
		". They will be included on the publication should your movie be published.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Any information that helped you during the making of the run, such as Lua scripts and memory addresses.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Subtitles and/or commentary, if you have them, are highly beneficial.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" You may also include a suggestion for a publication description and a suggestion for a publication screenshot.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"There is a preview function, so you can make sure your comments look as you intended. For any changes that need to be made, you can edit the text after submitting.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If you're a non-native English speaker, you can ask someone to help you translate from your native language.
	$LF
]div
[hr 
]hr
[h3 id=Troubleshooting 
	" Troubleshooting
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"You need to be logged in to submit movies. The login procedure is explained at the 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=login|href=/Account/Login)
	" page. After you've logged in, go 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=here to submit|href=/Submissions/Submit)
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Submissions may take some time to go through. Please wait after clicking Submit, as you may end up submitting several duplicate submissions by clicking it multiple times.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If your submission fails to go through, contact us via 
	[a class=intlink href=/Forum 
		"the forum
	]a
	" or 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Discord|href=/DiscordServer)
	" and we'll help you out.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=AfterSubmittingTheMovie 
	" After submitting the movie
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Your movie will appear in a few places:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" The 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=submission list|href=/Subs-List)
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" The 
		[a class=intlink href=/Forum 
			"discussion forums
		]a
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"When you submit a movie, a topic will automatically be created for your submission, allowing the community to comment on it. You are highly encouraged to follow the discussion and answer questions that may come up after submitting the movie. If you click “watch this topic for replies” at the page showing the discussion of the movie, the site will automatically e-mail you a notification when someone comments on your movie.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"A 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=Judge|href=/Staff)
	" will claim your movie and start looking into it, setting it to one of the following statuses:
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			"New (ready for judging)
		]em
		" ― The submission is unclaimed.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			"Judging Underway
		]em
		" ― The submission has been claimed by a Judge.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			"Delayed
		]em
		" ― The submission needs more time to be judged. This is often used at the submitter's request, for example if they are implementing improvements into their submission.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			"Needs More Info
		]em
		" ― The judge cannot make a decision until important information is provided.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			"Canceled
		]em
		" ― The author has withdrawn the submission, or a judge has prematurely rejected the movie. Movies canceled by the author can only be uncanceled by the same author.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			"Rejected
		]em
		" ― The movie was not considered good enough to be published. A rejection reason will be provided.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			"Publication Underway
		]em
		" ― The movie has been accepted and is currently being encoded.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		[em 
			"Published
		]em
		" ― The movie has been accepted and the official encode has been made.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	"Judges are human beings with lives, and may not always be available to process submissions. Please be patient if it is taking some time for your submission to be claimed or judged.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"If a submission is accepted, it will be accepted to one of three Classes. One can find out more information about these three classes in the 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Class|implicitdisplaytext=Class)
	" page and in the 
	(__wikiLink|href=/MovieRules|implicitdisplaytext=Movie Rules)
	".
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=UpdatingTheSubmissionFile 
	" Updating the submission file
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"If you later notice that your movie needs some 
	[em 
		"minor
	]em
	" changes, such as a new shortcut that is easy to incorporate, or a few more frames of input to reach the actual ending, you can request the submission file to be updated without having to cancel and submit a new movie. Upload your updated movie to 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Userfiles|implicitdisplaytext=Userfiles)
	" and make a post in your submission's discussion thread, announcing your improvement and linking to the userfile you've uploaded. Uploading to other file hosting sites is also allowed. For 
	[em 
		"major
	]em
	" changes, please cancel your submission and submit again.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"It is useful to elaborate on what your new movie has in it and why you want the submission to be updated. This operation requires a staff member to personally update your submission, so it may take a bit of time while it is being verified (regarding sync and other things). Alternatively you can send a private message to a 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=judge or a senior|href=/Staff)
	", containing your userfile link and all the notes about it, but public posts are preferred.
	$LF
]div
[hr 
]hr
[h3 id=FinalWords 
	" Final Words
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"All submissions are considered for publication, and we have standards for our publications that we hold each submission to. Please be mindful and accepting of critique on your submissions, and stay civil during discussions. Our intent is always to help you improve your skills, not to dissuade you from ever TASing again. We have 
	(__wikiLink|href=/Userfiles|implicitdisplaytext=Userfiles)
	", 
	[a class=intlink href=/Forum 
		"the forum
	]a
	", and 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=a Discord server|href=/DiscordServer)
	" that you can use to share your TAS projects without submitting them for judgement.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Users who flagrantly abuse the submission mechanism will have their submission privileges revoked at the discretion of the administration, and may be banned from the site entirely if their abuse warrants it.
]div
